14. Rxa3
{ 14.Bxa3! was probably even better, and if 14...Nc7 15.Bb2 Ne6 16.f4. White is a pawn down, but clearly d4 is weak and he has a certain initiative, which 16...f5 17.exf5 gxf5 18.Bd5 would but maintain. It’s by no means impossible that Qd2, Kh2 and a well-timed g4 could follow, or just Qe1-f2. }
