{ Richard Reti’s favourite square for the queen and a clear sign here that White is doing pretty well. }
16... a6
{ Skembris criticised this, but even after 16...Qb6 17.f4 Black is clearly worse, followed by f4-f5 or 17...f5 18.exf5 gxf5 19.Bd5 Kh8 20.Bxe6 Bxe6 21.Bxd4 Qc7 22.Rxa7, which wins a pawn for starters. }
