22... Bxe6 23. d5 Bd7 24. Rc1
{ It’s logical to want to push through c5, after which White might eventually obtain ideal central control with f4 and e5. }
24... a5
{ After 24...Qc7 Skembris even wondered about 25.c5!? dxc5 26.f4 with dangerous compensation for the pawn in the shape of White’s powerful centre. }
