26. Rb6 $1 Bc8 $2
{ Now Black is swept aside by a tsunami. He absolutely had to try 26...Qc5 27.Rxb7 Rxb7 28.Qxb7 Rd8 29.Rb1, grim though this would have been. }
27. c5 $1 { Another powerful pawn break on a dark square. } 27... dxc5 28. d6
Qd8 29. Rxc5
{ Just compare the difference in activity between the two forces! Unsurprisingly Black didn’t last much longer. }
29... a4 30. Rc7 Be6
{ Black’s exposed king would prove his undoing after 30...Bd7 31.e5! fxe5 32.Qxe5 and Bd5+. }
31. Qb4 { Not only attacking the a-pawn, but preparing Bf1-c4. } 31... Rf7 32.
Qxa4 $1 Ra8 { The defence is overloaded in the event of 32...Rxc7? 33.dxc7. }
