13... Qe7 14. f5 Bd7 15. g4 h6
{ Naturally Black has no desire to be completely overrun and at least this way he has the option to open the h-file for his rooks. }
16. h4 O-O-O 17. g5 Ne8
{ We can rarely remember Vishy in such a passive and grim position as Black – and after just 17 moves. Unable to crash through on the kingside, Magnus now combines increasing the pressure there with lining up the b4 break. }
18. Bd2 $5 hxg5 19. hxg5 Nc7 20. Ng4 Rdg8 21. Rh2
{ More simple chess. White wants to boss the open file. } 21... Qf8 22. Rdh1
Kb8 23. b4 $1 axb3 24. axb3 Nc8 25. Kb2 Qd8 26. Rh7
