{ 21...Nb4!? would have been consistent with Black’s last, but after 22.Qb3! White remains clearly for choice, as shown by 22...d5 23.a3 fxg5 24.hxg5 Rfc8 25.c5!, keeping lines closed on one flank, but not on the other where 25...Na6 26.Bxa6 Rxa6 27.g6 would begin to open them. }
